Magic Number Subnetting

Now, I think I've covered decent ground regarding the other two topics. And for us its a useful way to get in the door and calculate subnet masks and all this riffraff by ourselves. But when you're facing a real life exam, job or configuring your own router at your own house. Writing a binary chart and doing the conversions manually takes a lot of time and writing. lets face it, as much as i hate the idea of teaching and doing more math, doing it the easy way takes more outta you and me both in the long and short term. Thats why the magic number subnetting method exists, so we can do the necessary calculations inside our heads without writing a thesis dissertation when solving a networking problem. Admittedly, you will need a chart or two to pull this off correctly in your first few tries but as i showed in the previous sections certain factors will come into play to help you not only get used to pulling these numbers out of nowhere but making sure you save a lot of time in the process. Even doing this crudely will save you more time than doing it via the previous method in the classless section i was talking about. But as a spoiler alert, the magic number literally is a single value that gives you all the info you need about a subnet and to answer those pesky configuration problems. As we go over in depth on how to actually do it, its like if you were already figuring out the range of id cards you can put in your room you wouldn't necessarily need to draw the room and cards over and over, you'd use a computer and memorize a bit of values to do the heavy lifting for you.  

Just like in the classful subnetting section there's four key pieces of information we need to get using the magic number method:

Network Address
Broadcast Address
First Usable Host
Last Usable Host   

So all in all we're trying to reach the same destination but in a new context thanks to classless but using a huge shortcut via the magic number method. But to get back to the good stuff, as i said before charts might help you on your journey for this regard but as the more you deal with these numbers the more intuitive it gets so here are a few:

